Installation:

    git clone git://github.com/dubsgordon/vim_dotfiles.git ~/.vim 

Create symlinks:

    ln -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc

Switch to the `~/.vim` directory, and fetch submodules:

    cd ~/.vim
    git submodule init
    git submodule update


Add a new git submodule:

git submodule add http://github.location/bundle.git bundle/bundle-name
git add .
git commit -m "install bundle-name as submodule." 

Upgrade a bundle.. ie. fugitive

cd ~/.vim/bundle/fugitive
git pull origin master

OR

git submodule foreach git pull origin master




Note: command-t extension requires a build after update or install:
ALSO note that if using RVM, you should use system version of ruby which is
the ruby macvim is supporting

rvm use system

cd ~/.vim/bundle/command-t
bundle install
rake make

